President of Pentecostal Minister Forum (PMF) Bishop Chidi Anthony, has urged all Christians to see themselves as one family as well as pray together for the unity of the nation. Anthony stated this at the forum’s monthly general meeting at its headquarters, at Ijegun, Ikotun, Lagos State, where challenges facing the Christian religious body were addressed. He also stated that the part of the forum’s goals was to pray for the nation to overcome its many challenges, especially on the insecurity of the country. He also noted that the forum was committed to assisting the security operatives on security matters as well as help them in prayers. There’s global acknowledgement of  insecurity in Nigerians… 28 years jinx broken as Bello builds Kogi Govt House chapel Abidoye condemns infrastructure dilapidation, congestion in… Day church leaders, media professionals, others stood for… Speaking on the importance of the forum, Anthony noted that PMF is a collection of clerics of the gospel that are for the enhancement and effectiveness of their calling to the body of Christ to showcase the true character of a ministers. The speaker of the meeting Dr. Chris Ekeh, spoke on the causes of decay in church administration and management, which has led to the downfall of many churches. “The first assignment God gave man was the management of resources for the fulfillment of God’s vision on earth. Dreams determine your goals, your goals map out your actions, your action create results and the results bring your success,” he said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
